⸻

⚙️ Core Loop

while (system_active):

    inputs = gather_signals()

    candidates = explore(inputs, exploration_rate)

    scored = evaluate(candidates)

    reinforced = select(scored >= reinforcement_threshold)

    pruned = select(scored <= prune_threshold)

    update_memory(reinforced)

    decay(pruned)

    drift_score = detect_drift(memory, recent_outcomes)

    if drift_score > threshold:
        widen_exploration()
        tighten_pruning()

    output = best_current_paths()

    return output


⸻

🧠 Functions (Mapped to Pantheon)

1. explore()
	•	Owner: Spider
	•	Expands search space
	•	Introduces variation / new paths

⸻

2. evaluate()
	•	Owner: Hound + Mirror
	•	Scores based on:
	•	outcome quality
	•	repeatability
	•	invariant alignment

⸻

3. select()
	•	Filters:
	•	reinforce (keep + amplify)
	•	prune (decay/remove)

⸻

4. update_memory()
	•	Owner: EchoFrame + Mother Duck
	•	Stores:
	•	compressed pattern
	•	context
	•	success conditions

⸻

5. detect_drift()
	•	Owner: Badger (CAO)
	•	Looks for:
	•	rising variance without returns
	•	repeated failures
	•	overconfidence patterns

⸻

6. widen_exploration()
	•	Increase randomness when stuck or drifting

⸻

7. tighten_pruning()
	•	Remove weak signals faster under noise

⸻

📊 Scoring Model

score = (
    outcome_success * 0.4 +
    repeatability * 0.3 +
    efficiency * 0.2 +
    invariant_alignment * 0.1
)


⸻

🚨 Drift Detection

Trigger drift if:
	•	Success rate ↓ over last N iterations
	•	Exploration narrows prematurely
	•	Same paths reused without improvement
	•	Narrative > outcome (ego creep)

⸻

🧭 Modes

1. Exploration Mode
	•	High exploration_rate
	•	Loose pruning
	•	Used for new domains

2. Optimization Mode
	•	Lower exploration_rate
	•	Strong reinforcement
	•	Tight pruning

3. Recovery Mode
	•	Triggered by drift
	•	Reset partial memory weighting
	•	Re-expand search space

